ZH: 我们只能听之任之，因为我们没有更好的选择。
EN: We can only listen and accept it because we have no better option.

ZH: 当事情变得无法控制时，有时候最好的方法就是听之任之。
EN: When things get out of control, sometimes the best approach is to listen and accept it.

ZH: 他们不停地吵架，我只能听之任之，不想参与其中。
EN: They kept arguing, and I just had to listen and accept it without getting involved.

ZH: 遇到困难时，要学会听之任之，不要轻易放弃。
EN: When facing difficulties, we must learn to listen and accept it, and not give up easily.

ZH: 有时候事情不如我们开始的时候计划那么顺利，要学会听之任之，接受现实。
EN: Sometimes things don't go as smoothly as planned, we need to learn to listen and accept it, and face reality.

ZH: 不要为了一点点小事就生气，学会听之任之，放下自己的坚持。
EN: Don't get angry over little things, learn to listen and accept it, let go of your stubbornness.

ZH: 在等待结果的时候，我们只能听之任之，相信一切都会好起来的。
EN: While waiting for the outcome, we can only listen and accept it, believing that everything will turn out alright.

ZH: 他们有各自的意见，我只能听之任之，不想掺和他们的争论。
EN: They have their own opinions, and I just have to listen and accept it, not wanting to get involved in their arguments.

ZH: 做自己能做的事情，接受不能改变的事实，听之任之。
EN: Do what you can, accept the things that cannot be changed, listen and accept it.

ZH: 有时候我们遇到的问题是无法改变的，只能听之任之，让时间来解决。
EN: Sometimes the problems we encounter cannot be changed, we can only listen and accept it, and let time resolve it.

ZH: 当别人的选择让我们无法理解时，我们只能听之任之，尊重他们的决定。
EN: When someone's choices are incomprehensible to us, we can only listen and accept it, respecting their decisions.

ZH: 遇到突发情况时，要学会听之任之，不要过于紧张。
EN: When faced with unexpected situations, learn to listen and accept it, not to be too nervous.

ZH: 虽然我们不能控制一切，但我们可以学会听之任之，接受现实。
EN: Although we cannot control everything, we can learn to listen and accept it, accepting reality.

ZH: 不要试图干涉他人的选择，要学会听之任之，尊重他们的决定。
EN: Do not try to interfere with other people's choices, learn to listen and accept it, respecting their decisions.

ZH: 面对挑战时，要学会听之任之，不要轻易放弃。
EN: When facing challenges, learn to listen and accept it, do not give up easily.

ZH: 有时候我们需要学会听之任之，接受生活的起起伏伏。
EN: Sometimes we need to learn to listen and accept it, accepting the ups and downs of life.

ZH: 当他们的看法与我们不一样时，我们只能听之任之，尊重他们的观点。
EN: When their views are different from ours, we can only listen and accept it, respecting their opinions.

ZH: 面对失败，要学会听之任之，不要灰心丧气。
EN: When faced with failure, learn to listen and accept it, do not lose heart.

ZH: 无论发生什么事情，要学会听之任之，接受现实。
EN: No matter what happens, learn to listen and accept it, accepting reality.
